# .raccoonignore - Files to exclude from syncing to the Wombat
#
# This file controls which files are NOT synced to the device during
# `raccoon sync`, `raccoon run`, `raccoon calibrate`, etc.
#
# Note: Files listed here will still be PULLED from the device during
# codegen, so generated hardware definitions stay in sync.
#
# Syntax:
#   - One pattern per line
#   - Lines starting with # are comments
#   - Patterns use fnmatch/glob syntax (*.pyc, __pycache__, etc.)
#   - Directory names match anywhere in the path

# Hardware definitions (generated on device, pulled during codegen)
# Don't overwrite device-specific calibration with local files
.git
.idea